description.0: Spider-Man finds himself at the center of a "gangland convention", where his civilian identity is the main bounty. Will the biggest and baddest of New York's crime families unite into one crime syndicate? Green Goblin levels the playing field against Peter Parker, and the outcome of this game is sudden death!
description.1: George Perez's mysterious cover practically forces you to open up the comic and find out what's going on. Mission accomplished.
description.2: It's never an easy day for America's Champion. Steve Rogers may be a super hero, but that doesn't exempt him from ordinary people problems. Can Cap find a balance between Sharon Carter and the new Veda? Plus: what does General Lyle Dekker know that Captain America Doesn't? Find out in One Day in Newfoundland!
description.3: The Mole Man and the Subterraneans are on an all-out heist for the residents of New York City! Special cameo appearance by Daredevil, Man Without Fear!
description.4: The Ruby Scarab has changed Carol, allowing her to transform into Ms. Marvel at will! And she'll have to put this new mastery to the test, when a visit with her family is interrupted by the villainous Sapper!
description.5: NITRO IS BACK! How can Mar-Vell defeat a foe with the power to make anything and EVERYTHING explode?
description.9: Richard Rider's personal life is getting in the way of being Nova! Will family conflict interfere with Nova's mission to take down Yellow Claw?
description.13: While in the United States as a foreign exchange student, Captain Britain realizes his roommate is PETER PARKER!
description.16: Howard is able to stave off Dr. Bong's latest attack...while he's taking a shower? But that's not all! Can Howard save new friend Sudd from his monstrous transformation?
description.17: The return of Green Goblin? Peter gets concerned for Harry Osborn when he finds his psychiatrist's office in a state of disarray. Plus, Aunt May faces a health scare, and Flash Thompson gets involved with Spidey's fiercest villain. There aren't enough hours in a day for the threats Spider-Man faces in this issue!
description.18: Wasp becomes possessed and takes down her fellow Avengers after touching her newly reassembled birthday gift from YELLOW JACKET -- Dr. Spectrum's Power Prism!
description.19: The Guardians of the Galaxy have time traveled to the present day to save the future! Meanwhile, the Wasp's fashion show is interrupted by a super-villain robbery!
description.20: Nick Fury has some new recruits that need some breaking-in. Can Cap and Falc train the next generation of S.H.I.E.L.D. Agents? How will the veteran super heroes pass on the torch! Find out in this awesome new issue!
description.21: Mutants of Los Angeles tremble at the might of the Sentinels! The Champions do battle to protect their own mutant members. But will the team trust the 'evil' mutants who claim to be victims of the Sentinels' pursuit? Darkstar shows the full range of her powers...and the display's frightening!
description.22: Is the known as Paladin a hero or a villain? He's a mercenary on the trail of Purple Man, the same as Daredevil. But will he be a friend or foe to DD?
description.23: Druig has escaped his confinement and has entered the Pyramid of Winds! Can Ikaris destroy his cousin before Druig launches a massive attack against the Celestials?! Never fear, for hope springs ETERNAL!
description.24: Tension on the high seas! Hulk is on a deserted island...where his ship is attacked by Captain Barracuda!
description.25: Iron Man takes on Midas' Mechanoids.
description.26: Thor returns to Earth as Donald Blake once more, only to run into trouble with Damocles! Can the God of Thunder stop the menacing Damocles before he gets away with his stolen lot?
description.27: Janus, Son of Dracula, is back and an adult! Why is he targeting his father?
description.28: With the Fantastic Four broken up, Ben Grimm reminisces on the good and bad times he and the team shared throughout the years. A retrospective issue any True Believer will enjoy!
description.33: Han and Chewie head out to pay their debt to Jabba, when they're attacked by pirates!
description.35: What if you had a scientific solution that could turn you invisible? Would you do good, or exploit its potential? Find out in H. G. Wells' The Invisible Man!
description.40: Ms. Marvel battles the Elementals alongside Hecate! Can the pair retrieve the dangerous ruby scarab before the Elementals use it to destroy Cape Canaveral?!
description.42: Nova and Nick Fury are in for it with Yellow Claw! Meanwhile, what will Richard Rider do when his father is arrested?
description.44: With Iron Fist down for the count, it's up to Spider-Man and the Daughters of the Dragon to eliminate Steel Serpent! Misty Knight and Colleen Wing kick serious Kung Fu tail, as they track down Iron Fist's worst foe with Spidey's help. Will Iron Fist receive the powers of the Dragon once again?
description.47: Back in New York City, Howard struggles to make sense of his new life as a human. And when Dr. Bong discovers that Howard survived, he vows once and for all to end Howard's existence! How will Howard the Duck finally stop the relentless Dr. Bong!?
description.48: Druig, the evil cousin of Ikaris, seeks out the means to destroy the Celestials once and for all! But even he can't predict that the secret lies with...Ikaris himself! What lengths will Druig take to steal such information from his cousin?
description.49: Doc Samson and The Rhino exchange blows when Rhino unleashes terror on public transportation. But will Samson be able to subdue his foe without the help of his allies?
description.50: The invincible Iron Man challenged by the combined might of the Gaurdsman, the Wraith, and Jack of Hearts! It's time for the ultimate showdown!
description.52: It's a body-snatching battle when three men try to inhabit one body! Whose spirit will belong to the Destroyer?
description.53: What if the Fantastic Four had different super-powers?
description.54: With Emperor D'Ken threatening to destroy the universe while trying to utilize the power of the M'Kraan Crystal, the X-Men and the Starjammers discover that when the specific stars come into alignment, the crystal will become available to D'Ken.
description.55: Fighting fire with fire! Johnny is confronted by the original Human Torch and engages in a heated battle! Meanwhile, A.I. Quasimodo longs to be human, but is it fated to be?
description.61: Punisher reveals his history with Hitman after he and Spider-Man hit a dead end. Will J. Jonah Jameson be safe from the fury of the People's Liberation Front? And what happens when Harry Osborn's psychiatrist pushes him a little too far? A Punisher/Spider-Man team-up you have to see to believe!
description.62: The Nefaria Supreme Saga. The Avengers are fighting back against their most dangerous foe yet! But will their combined forces be enough to ward off Nefaria's dark magic?
description.63: Blazing battle with a surprising finish! Captain America versus the Human Torch!
description.65: H. Rider Haggard's She: A History of Adventure chronicles the quest of two explorers in search of an enchanted, immortal queen. Read its comic adaptation today!
description.67: The conclusion of the adaptation of A New Hope!  Can the Rebels destroy the Death Star?
description.68: Captain Marvel forms a powerful alliance with Black Bolt on what seems to be a mission that will lead to sudden death…
description.70: Strangeness at Stonehenge! After Alicia’s frightening bout as a spider-woman, Ben and Alicia are determined to end their English holiday on a high note. But upon their arrival at Stonehenge, the couple is met by elemental demons! Enter Modred the Mystic, the only sorcerer who can defeat these foul spirits!
description.71: Nova's on a mission to save the Burley brothers! And when Nick Fury asks for Nova's assistance in the rescue, Richard just can't say no!
description.72: It's back to a life of reporting for Carol Danvers--or so she thinks! Drawn away from a NASA story to help friends in need, Carol is suddenly ambushed by Olympian soldiers made of the earth itself!
description.73: Death-Stalker has created a new Smasher. And his orders are to destroy Daredevil!
description.74: Makarri, Ikaris, and Zuras face off against Dromedan together, but even their combined might seems helpless against him! But can Sersi's arrival turn the tide of the battle?
description.75: Hulk befriends a group of ex-circus performers. Will this be a clan the Green Goliath can call his own?
description.76: Hounded by his enemies! Torn between his friends! The Armored Avenger battles alone! Will Tony Stark
description.77: Thor battles the Destroyer with Sif and Karnilla by his side! But what's causing Karnilla to duck out of the battle early?
description.78: Resurrection! The Son of Dracula is back...but sometimes dead is better!
description.79: The Molecule Man has taken over Mister Fantastic's body, and Reed can only fight back with his mind! Is his psyche strong enough to prevent Molecule Man from destroying his teammates? All is revealed with a shocking twist.
description.82: The People's Liberation Front is back on the scene, and this time they mean business! After the PLF tries to rob a firearms shop, the Punisher intervenes. The return of Hitman spells big trouble for J. Jonah Jameson and Marla Madison!
description.83: The Avengers are no match against Count Nefaria. The Count is dropping buildings, taking names, and...becoming immortal?
description.84: Captain America is the people's champion. But that's only the image, who is Captain America, really? Better question: "Who is Steve Rogers?"
description.85: Doctor Doom is up to his usual tricks; he has unleashed a toxic neuro gas that has taken over the minds of the Champions! Beast of the X-Men and Magneto are miraculously unaffected; will the two mutants unite to take down Doom before he releases his mind control gas to the population at large?
description.86: With the stolen plans, the Rebels begin their attack on the Death Star.
description.88: The Steel Serpent has left a calling card for Iron Fist...and Peter Parker delivers the message! Spider-Man and Iron Fist team-up against unimaginable evil; will Misty Knight become a casualty in the process? Plus, what happens when Danny Rand loses the power of the Iron Fist?
description.89: While a terribly wounded Toro lies in a hospital bed, the Human Torch recounts the young hero's origin story.
description.91: Dr. Bong's devious plan to experiment on Howard the Duck is foiled by Beverly and her new friend Fifi. But then the unexpected happens - Howard has transformed into a human! It's Howard the Human!
description.95: Adapting Wilkie Collins' The Moonstone! A mystery surrounding a jewel theft sets Sergeant Cuff into motion!
description.97: The Thing and Spider-Woman face their greatest challenge yet! Hydra’s experimental ‘spider mutations’ have ravaged Alicia’s mind and body. Can Thing save Alicia from herself, or has she already become more spider than woman? The Invisible Girl provides much needed backup!
description.98: Saved by MODOK!? Carol gets caught in the middle of an A.I.M. civil war, and whichever side wins, the Earth loses! Can Ms. Marvel hope to stop MODOK and Deathbird--at the same time?
description.99: Nova battles Sandman at his old high school in an attempt to save his classmate's older brother, Samuel Burley. Meanwhile, Charles Rider's financial troubles send him down an uncertain path.

6.text: Behold! The origin of the Black Panther cult! What is the legacy T’Challa, Prince of Wakanda, was born into? And what do the Black Panthers protect? General Jakarra taps into a precious Wakandan resource…with disastrous results.

7.text: The Thing, sucked into a vortex of the Bermuda Triangle! While visiting Cape Canaveral, a routine appearance for Ben Grimm turns into a battle with prehistoric beasts. Meet Skull the Slayer and his crew of scientists, a time-displaced lot trapped in the world of dinosaurs. Will Grimm and the lost adventurers finally find their meal ticket home?

9.text: Richard Rider's personal life is getting in the way of being Nova! Will family conflict interfere with Nova's mission to take down Yellow Claw?

15.text: The Red Guardian attacks! The Defenders go on the defensive against their former partner, now under the control of the Presence.

22.text: Is the known as Paladin a hero or a villain?  He's a mercenary on the trail of Purple Man, the same as Daredevil.  But will he be a friend or foe to DD?

29.text: In one of the most dark, thrilling issues of this series, Spider-Man, Razorback, and Flash Thompson are trapped in a dungeon accompanied by a ticking bomb…placed by none other than the Hate-Monger!

36.text: Shang-Chi's deadliest foes return, this time as pawns of Marvel's master of macabre villainy -- DOCTOR DOOM!

40.text: Ms. Marvel battles the Elementals alongside Hecate! Can the pair retrieve the dangerous ruby scarab before the Elementals use it to destroy Cape Canaveral?!

41.text: Toro returns to the United States. Then...the Invaders vs. Scarlet Scarab!

42.text: Nova and Nick Fury are in for it with Yellow Claw! Meanwhile, what will Richard Rider do when his father is arrested?

43.text: The Thing's adventure across the Atlantic Ocean continues! This time, he pairs up with Nighthawk to defeat a monstrous menace! But is this strange creature truly as menacing as it looks?

45.text: Doctor Strange realizes that the world is in its current state because the Ancient One is no longer One with the Universe!

46.text: With their ship destroyed, the Defenders scramble to the surface for safety.

51.text: Blastoff with Torpedo! Want to learn all about Brock Jones and his remarkable abilities? Start with this explosive issue!

56.text: Spider-Man is shocked when an unknown man named Razorback ambushes him!

58.text: Shang-Chi might be burned in the aftermath to the “Phoenix Gambit”! Plus, who is the Angel of Doom?

64.text: On the hunt for Misty Knight, Power Man breaks into the home of Danny Rand and finds Colleen Wing! Their confrontation leads to battle, and Power Man going up against Iron Fist! Outnumbered and outmatched, Power Man struggles to take on the martial arts of the Young Dragon!

68.text: Captain Marvel forms a powerful alliance with Black Bolt on what seems to be a mission that will lead to sudden death…

69.text: Panther and Abner seek out the Water of Immortality in faraway Samurai City. In Wakanda, General Jakarra stages a mutiny against T’Challa- the Black Panther…and Jakarra’s half-brother!

70.text: Strangeness at Stonehenge! After Alicia’s frightening bout as a spider-woman, Ben and Alicia are determined to end their English holiday on a high note. But upon their arrival at Stonehenge, the couple is met by elemental demons! Enter Modred the Mystic, the only sorcerer who can defeat these foul spirits!

71.text: Nova's on a mission to save the Burley brothers! And when Nick Fury asks for Nova's assistance in the rescue, Richard just can't say no!

72.text: It's back to a life of reporting for Carol Danvers--or so she thinks! Drawn away from a NASA story to help friends in need, Carol is suddenly ambushed by Olympian soldiers made of the earth itself!

73.text: Death-Stalker has created a new Smasher.  And his orders are to destroy Daredevil!

80.text: "The Legion of Light", a new powerful cult, has taken New York City by the throat. Spidey, partnered with Flash Thompson, must find a way to not only discover the origins of this rising group, but also take down their two leaders, Brother Power and Sister Sun.

90.text: Lord Vashti explains to the Defenders the device that’s polluting Atlantis with radiation.

92.text: Shang-Chi squares off against War-Yore, the Murder Master, once more!

96.text: Mutant magnate Magneto expresses his desire for world domination. Will Marvel’s heaviest hitting villain team-up with Doctor Doom? And why is Magneto seeking the aid of the Avengers? All this and more answered in the next exciting issue of Super-Villain Team-Up!

97.text: The Thing and Spider-Woman face their greatest challenge yet! Hydra’s experimental ‘spider mutations’ have ravaged Alicia’s mind and body. Can Thing save Alicia from herself, or has she already become more spider than woman? The Invisible Girl provides much needed backup!

98.text: Saved by MODOK!? Carol gets caught in the middle of an A.I.M. civil war, and whichever side wins, the Earth loses! Can Ms. Marvel hope to stop MODOK and Deathbird--at the same time?

99.text: Nova battles Sandman at his old high school in an attempt to save his classmate's older brother, Samuel Burley. Meanwhile, Charles Rider's financial troubles send him down an uncertain path.
